# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#  DrFX Quant — Environment Configuration
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# Server
PORT=3000

# Security — generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
JWT_SECRET=generate_with_openssl_rand_hex_32

# Admin account (auto-created on first run)
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@drfx.com
ADMIN_PASSWORD=your_secure_password

# PostgreSQL
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://drfx:password@localhost:5432/drfx_quant
DB_USER=drfx
DB_PASS=password
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=drfx_quant

# AI Assistant (optional) — get a key at https://openrouter.ai
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_openrouter_api_key_here

# Crypto Payments (optional) — get keys at https://nowpayments.io
NOWPAYMENTS_API_KEY=your_nowpayments_api_key_here
NOWPAYMENTS_IPN_SECRET=your_nowpayments_ipn_secret_here

# Email confirmation (sign-up codes) — configure easily via: sudo bash manage.sh
# When SMTP_HOST is set, new sign-ups must confirm a 6-digit code emailed to
# them. Leave SMTP_HOST blank to disable (instant sign-up). Works with Resend,
# SendGrid, Mailgun, Gmail (app password), Supabase SMTP, etc.
SMTP_HOST=
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_SECURE=false
SMTP_USER=
SMTP_PASS=
SMTP_FROM=DrFX Quant <no-reply@yourdomain.com>

# ── Ecosystem additions (Phase 1) ──────────────────────────────
# TradingView webhook shared secret — generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
# Until set, /api/webhooks/tradingview rejects every request.
TRADINGVIEW_WEBHOOK_SECRET=generate_with_openssl_rand_hex_32
# @username of the channel signals broadcast to (must exist as a 'channel' chat)
SIGNAL_CHANNEL_USERNAME=signals

# The following are used only AFTER you wire the security middleware / refresh
# tokens per INTEGRATION.md (require `npm i helmet express-rate-limit cookie-parser`).
NODE_ENV=development
# Comma-separated CORS allowlist, e.g. https://app.yourdomain.com,https://yourdomain.com
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=
# Access/refresh token lifetimes (refresh-token auth is opt-in; see INTEGRATION.md)
ACCESS_TTL=15m
REFRESH_TTL_DAYS=30

# ── Live Trading: WebRTC SFU + TURN (high-FPS 30/60 streaming) ──
# These are written AUTOMATICALLY by:  sudo bash setup-live-sfu.sh
# (it installs mediasoup + coturn, detects the public IP, generates the secret,
#  opens the firewall, and flips LIVE_SFU=on). Until they exist, Live Trading
#  falls back to the low-FPS (~15) socket frame relay. Do NOT set LIVE_SFU=on by
#  hand unless mediasoup is actually installed AND coturn is running, or the app
#  will advertise a media plane that isn't there.
#
# LIVE_SFU=on
# SFU_ANNOUNCED_IP=YOUR_PUBLIC_IPV4               # public IP advertised in ICE candidates
# SFU_RTC_MIN_PORT=40000                          # mediasoup media UDP range (open in firewall)
# SFU_RTC_MAX_PORT=40100
# TURN_HOST=YOUR_PUBLIC_IPV4                       # coturn host (usually the same public IP)
# TURN_SECRET=generate_with_openssl_rand_hex_32   # MUST equal static-auth-secret in /etc/turnserver.conf

# ── Chat translation: LibreTranslate (self-hosted, provider-agnostic) ──
# These are written AUTOMATICALLY by:  sudo bash setup-translation.sh
# (it installs LibreTranslate in a venv, runs it under PM2 on 127.0.0.1:5000,
#  and points the app at it). The feature DEGRADES GRACEFULLY: until these are
#  set and the engine is reachable, the app simply hides the translate UI — chat
#  is unaffected. Original messages are never modified; translations are cached
#  in the message_translations table and shown as an advisory layer.
#
# TRANSLATE_PROVIDER=libretranslate               # libretranslate | none
# TRANSLATE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5000             # base URL of the engine (loopback)
# TRANSLATE_API_KEY=                              # only if your engine requires a key
# TRANSLATE_TIMEOUT_MS=8000                       # per-request timeout

# ── Quant Option: REAL market-price settlement (opt-in) ────────
# By default Quant Option uses its provably-fair SIMULATED price engine (no key,
# zero external calls). Set QUANTOPTION_REAL_PRICES=true to settle positions
# against REAL market prices instead: crypto (BTC/ETH/SOL/BNB-USDT) via Binance's
# free public API (no key), and FX/metals (XAU/EUR/GBP-USD) via TwelveData (free
# key at https://twelvedata.com). Crypto settles at 1-second fidelity; FX/metals
# at 1-minute, so prefer >=3min expiries for FX/metals. With the flag off (or
# absent) these vars are ignored and Quant Option behavior is unchanged.
# QUANTOPTION_REAL_PRICES=false
# TWELVEDATA_API_KEY=your_twelvedata_api_key_here
